    "status": "draft",
    "id": "c11443ee-542f-4442-b28d-2d224342be37",
    "description": {
      "purpose": "This dataset provides comprehensive HDB resale flat transaction records in Singapore from January 2017 onwards, enabling market analysis, price trend monitoring, and informed decision-making for property buyers, sellers, real estate professionals, and policy makers. It serves as the authoritative source for understanding Singapore's public housing resale market dynamics.",
      "usage": "Consumers can analyze resale price trends by town, flat type, floor area, and storey range to assess market valuations. The data supports comparative market analysis for property valuation, research on housing affordability, and development of pricing models. Access is available via CSV download or REST API queries using the dataset ID for programmatic integration.",
      "limitations": "Resale prices are indicative only as actual transaction values depend on multiple factors including flat condition and buyer-seller negotiations. The dataset excludes transactions that may not reflect full market prices, such as sales between relatives or partial share transfers. A business rule constraint requires resale prices not to exceed 2 million SGD for data quality purposes."
    }
  }
}